Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Red paint at neck join. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Thestor. From same die as Delos TD3328. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 80, 14
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0851)
